            "content": "# Todo App — Build Plan\n\n## Product Vision\n\nThis is not just another todo list. It's a fast, resilient personal task manager that works seamlessly whether you're online or offline. Built with a React + Vite frontend and a FastAPI + SQLite backend, the app gives users a fluid, tactile experience for capturing, organizing, and completing tasks. Drag-and-drop reordering, inline editing, and instant optimistic updates make the interface feel native — not like a web page pretending to be an app.\n\nThe offline-first architecture is the app's defining quality. Users can create, edit, reorder, and delete tasks with zero network connectivity. When the connection returns, a conflict-aware sync engine reconciles local and remote state automatically. SQLite on the backend keeps deployment simple — a single binary and a single file — while IndexedDB on the client mirrors the full task store locally. The result is an app that is always available, always responsive, and never loses your work.\n\nBeyond the basics, the app adds thoughtful polish: keyboard shortcuts for power users, smooth animations on reorder, a dark/light theme that respects system preferences, and a clean, opinionated visual design that makes the mundane act of managing tasks feel surprisingly satisfying. Drawing inspiration from Things 3 and Linear, the UI uses generous whitespace, subtle depth cues, and delightful micro-interactions.\n\n## Technical Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│           React + Vite SPA          │\n│  ┌───────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  │\n│  │ Task Store │  │  Sync Engine   │  │\n│  │ (Zustand)  │──│ (ServiceWorker)│  │\n│  └─────┬─────┘  └───────┬────────┘  │\n│        │                │           │\n│  ┌─────▼─────┐  ┌───────▼────────┐  │\n│  │  IndexedDB │  │  Offline Queue │  │\n│  │  (Dexie)   │  │  (Dexie table) │  │\n│  └────────────┘  └────────────────┘  │\n└──────────────────┬──────────────────┘\n                   │ REST + JSON\n┌──────────────────▼──────────────────┐\n│          FastAPI Backend            │\n│  ┌────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  │\n│  │  Routers   │  │  Pydantic     │  │\n│  │  /api/v1/* │  │  Models       │  │\n│  └─────┬──────┘  └───────────────┘  │\n│  ┌─────▼──────┐  ┌───────────────┐  │\n│  │  Service   │  │  Sync Service │  │\n│  │  Layer     │  │  (versioned)  │  │\n│  └─────┬──────┘  └───────────────┘  │\n│  ┌─────▼──────┐                     │\n│  │  SQLite    │                     │\n│  │  (aiosqlite)│                    │\n│  └────────────┘                     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Frontend:** React 18+ with TypeScript, Vite for bundling, Zustand for state management, Dexie.js for IndexedDB access, @dnd-kit for drag-and-drop, Framer Motion for animations, Tailwind CSS for styling. A service worker handles offline caching and background sync.\n\n**Backend:** FastAPI with Python 3.12+, aiosqlite for async SQLite access, Pydantic v2 for validation. The API follows RESTful conventions with a `/api/v1/` prefix. A lightweight sync protocol uses version counters per-item to resolve conflicts on reconnect.\n\n**Data Model:** Each todo item carries an `id` (UUID), `title`, `description`, `completed` (bool), `position` (float for fractional indexing), `priority` (int 0-3), `due_date` (optional ISO date), `created_at`, `updated_at`, and a `version` counter for conflict detection.\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 1: Project Skeleton & Core Backend\n\n### Scope\n- Initialize the monorepo structure with frontend and backend directories\n- Set up Vite + React + TypeScript with strict tsconfig and Tailwind CSS\n- Set up FastAPI with project structure (routers, models, services, repository, database)\n- Create the SQLite schema and database initialization\n- Implement CRUD API endpoints for todo items\n- Implement reorder endpoint for position updates\n- Add comprehensive input validation with Pydantic\n- Write backend tests with pytest\n- Configure CORS and dev server proxying\n\n### Deliverables\n- `backend/main.py` — FastAPI application entry point with CORS middleware\n- `backend/database.py` — async SQLite connection management with aiosqlite\n- `backend/models.py` — SQLite table definitions\n- `backend/schemas.py` — Pydantic v2 request/response models\n- `backend/repository.py` — TodoRepository with all DB operations\n- `backend/services.py` — Business logic layer\n- `backend/routes/todos.py` — REST API endpoints\n- `backend/tests/test_todos.py` — pytest test suite for all endpoints\n- `backend/requirements.txt` — Python dependencies\n- `frontend/` — Vite + React + TypeScript scaffold with Tailwind CSS configured\n- `frontend/package.json`, `frontend/tsconfig.json`, `frontend/vite.config.ts`\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Running `cd backend && pip install -r requirements.txt && python -m uvicorn main:app` starts the server on port 8000\n- `GET /health` returns 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n- `POST /api/v1/todos` with `{\"title\": \"Buy milk\"}` returns 201 with JSON body containing `id`, `title`, `completed`, `position`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `version`\n- `GET /api/v1/todos` returns 200 with a JSON array of all todos sorted by `position` ascending\n- `GET /api/v1/todos/{id}` returns 200 with the specific todo, or 404 with `{\"detail\": \"Todo not found\"}`\n- `PUT /api/v1/todos/{id}` with `{\"title\": \"Buy oat milk\", \"completed\": true}` returns 200 with the updated todo and incremented `version`\n- `DELETE /api/v1/todos/{id}` returns 204 and the todo is no longer returned by GET\n- `PATCH /api/v1/todos/{id}/reorder` with `{\"position\": 2.5}` returns 200 with updated position\n- `POST /api/v1/todos` with `{\"title\": \"\"}` returns 422 with validation error\n- `POST /api/v1/todos` with title exceeding 200 characters returns 422 with validation error\n- Running `cd backend && python -m pytest` passes with 80%+ coverage\n- Running `cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev` starts Vite dev server on port 5173\n- Frontend renders a heading \"Todo App\" at `http://localhost:5173`\n- TypeScript compiles with zero errors in strict mode\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use `aiosqlite` for async SQLite — do NOT use SQLAlchemy or SQLModel (keep it lightweight)\n- Repository pattern: routes → services → repository → database\n- Use float-based positioning: when inserting between items at positions 2.0 and 3.0, new position = 2.5\n- Use UUIDs (uuid7 preferred) as primary keys to support offline ID generation later\n- CORS: allow `http://localhost:5173` in development\n- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` with `TestClient` for API tests\n- Pydantic v2 models: `TodoCreate`, `TodoUpdate`, `TodoResponse`, `TodoReorder`\n- Database schema: create table in `database.py` on startup (no migration framework needed for SQLite)\n- Include a `version` integer column (default 1) for optimistic concurrency control\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 2: Core Frontend — Task List & CRUD UI\n\n### Scope\n- Build the main task list view with a clean, modern design\n- Implement add task form with inline input\n- Implement task completion toggle with checkbox\n- Implement inline task editing (double-click to edit title)\n- Implement task deletion with confirmation\n- Connect frontend to backend API with a typed API client\n- Add loading and error states\n- Establish the visual design system (colors, typography, spacing, shadows)\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/types/todo.ts` — TypeScript types matching backend schemas\n- `frontend/src/api/todoApi.ts` — Typed fetch wrapper for all endpoints\n- `frontend/src/store/todoStore.ts` — Zustand store with immer middleware and all CRUD actions\n- `frontend/src/components/TodoList.tsx` — Main list container\n- `frontend/src/components/TodoItem.tsx` — Individual task row with checkbox, edit, delete\n- `frontend/src/components/AddTodo.tsx` — Inline task creation input\n- `frontend/src/components/EmptyState.tsx` — Shown when no tasks exist\n- `frontend/src/components/ErrorBanner.tsx` — Error notification banner\n- `frontend/src/components/LoadingSpinner.tsx` — Loading indicator\n- Tailwind CSS configuration with custom color palette and design tokens\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- App loads and displays todos fetched from the backend API\n- User can type a task title and press Enter to add it — the task appears in the list immediately\n- Pressing Enter with an empty input does nothing (no empty todos created)\n- User can click a checkbox to toggle task completion — completed tasks show strikethrough with a CSS transition\n- User can double-click a task title to enter inline edit mode — title becomes an editable input\n- Pressing Enter in edit mode saves the change; pressing Escape cancels and reverts\n- Clicking outside the edit input saves the change (blur handler)\n- An empty title in edit mode is rejected with a red border and validation message\n- Each todo has a delete button (trash icon) visible on hover — clicking it removes the todo\n- When no todos exist, a friendly empty state is shown with the message \"No todos yet\"\n- While data loads from the API, a spinner or skeleton is shown\n- If the API is unreachable, an error banner appears with a descriptive message\n- The UI has clear visual hierarchy: header area, input area, list area with proper spacing\n- Todo titles longer than 200 characters are rejected with client-side validation\n- All interactive elements have visible hover and focus states\n- The UI is visually polished — proper spacing, typography, and color palette (not default browser styles)\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Zustand store with immer middleware for ergonomic immutable updates\n- API client: thin fetch wrapper with base URL from `VITE_API_URL` env var (default `http://localhost:8000`)\n- Implement optimistic updates: update the UI immediately, then sync to the backend; roll back on failure\n- Use `React.memo` on `TodoItem` to prevent unnecessary re-renders\n- Tailwind CSS: configure custom colors, fonts, and spacing in `tailwind.config.ts`\n- Keep components focused: each under 150 lines\n- Error handling: catch network errors and display user-friendly messages, never raw error objects\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 3: Drag-and-Drop Reordering & Animations\n\n### Scope\n- Add drag-and-drop reordering to the task list using @dnd-kit\n- Implement smooth animations during drag operations\n- Persist new order to the backend via batch reorder API\n- Add keyboard-accessible reordering (Alt+Up/Down)\n- Add framer-motion animations for add, remove, and reorder transitions\n- Visual feedback during drag (placeholder, shadow, scale)\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/components/SortableTodoList.tsx` — dnd-kit powered sortable list\n- `frontend/src/components/SortableTodoItem.tsx` — Sortable wrapper for TodoItem\n- `frontend/src/components/DragHandle.tsx` — Visible drag affordance with grip icon\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useTodoReorder.ts` — Hook encapsulating reorder logic\n- Updated `todoStore.ts` with optimistic reorder and rollback\n- Updated `todoApi.ts` with batch reorder support\n- Backend `PUT /api/v1/todos/reorder` batch endpoint\n- Animation integration with framer-motion across all list mutations\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Each todo displays a drag handle (grip dots icon) on the left side\n- Grabbing the drag handle and dragging vertically reorders the list in real time\n- The dragged item has a subtle shadow/elevation effect and slight scale increase while being dragged\n- A colored line indicator shows where the item will be dropped\n- After dropping, the new order persists across page refreshes (saved to backend)\n- User can focus a todo and press Alt+Up or Alt+Down to move it up/down — the item animates to its new position\n- Adding a new todo plays a slide-in animation from the top\n- Deleting a todo plays a fade-out + collapse animation\n- Reordering plays a smooth layout shift animation (no teleporting)\n- Dragging the first item to the last position works correctly\n- Dragging the last item to the first position works correctly\n- The batch reorder endpoint `PUT /api/v1/todos/reorder` accepts `[{\"id\": \"...\", \"position\": 1.0}, ...]` and updates all atomically\n- Reordering 20+ items feels smooth with no visible jank\n- Touch devices can long-press to initiate drag (mobile-friendly)\n- Screen readers announce position changes: \"Task moved to position 3 of 7\"\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use `@dnd-kit/core` and `@dnd-kit/sortable` with both PointerSensor and KeyboardSensor\n- Optimistic updates: reorder local state immediately, sync to server, revert on failure with toast notification\n- Use `framer-motion` `<AnimatePresence>` for exit animations and `layout` prop for reorder animations\n- Batch reorder: send full position list after drag ends (more reliable than single-item updates)\n- Position recalculation: after reorder, assign sequential positions (1.0, 2.0, 3.0...) to avoid float precision drift\n- ARIA: use `aria-roledescription=\"sortable\"` and announce position changes via live region\n- Use `touch-action: none` on drag handles for mobile compatibility\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 4: Task Details, Priority & Filtering\n\n### Scope\n- Add an expandable detail panel for each task\n- Support task descriptions (multi-line text)\n- Add due dates with a date picker\n- Add priority levels (none, low, medium, high) with color coding\n- Add filter tabs (All, Active, Completed) with count badges\n- Implement instant search with highlighted matches\n- Add bulk actions: mark all complete, clear completed\n- Add progress visualization and task count summary\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/components/TaskDetail.tsx` — Expandable detail panel\n- `frontend/src/components/DatePicker.tsx` — Lightweight date picker component\n- `frontend/src/components/PriorityBadge.tsx` — Colored priority indicator\n- `frontend/src/components/FilterBar.tsx` — Filter tabs with count badges\n- `frontend/src/components/SearchInput.tsx` — Search input with debounced filtering\n- `frontend/src/components/BulkActions.tsx` — Bulk action toolbar\n- `frontend/src/components/ProgressIndicator.tsx` — \"5 of 12 done\" with progress bar\n- `frontend/src/components/HighlightedText.tsx` — Search match highlighting\n- Updated backend models and schema to add `description`, `due_date`, `priority` fields\n- Updated API endpoints to accept and return new fields\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- User can click a task to expand its detail panel showing description, due date, and priority\n- User can add/edit a multi-line description in the detail panel\n- User can set a due date using a date picker; overdue tasks show a red indicator\n- User can set priority (none/low/medium/high); each level has a distinct color (grey/blue/orange/red)\n- Three filter tabs appear above the list: \"All (7)\", \"Active (5)\", \"Completed (2)\" with live counts\n- Clicking \"Active\" shows only incomplete todos; \"Completed\" shows only completed todos\n- The active filter tab has a distinct visual style (underline or background highlight)\n- Search input filters todos by title as the user types (debounced 200ms), case-insensitive\n- Matching text is highlighted with a `<mark>` element in search results\n- Search with no results shows \"No todos match your search\"\n- A \"Mark all complete\" checkbox in the header toggles all todos\n- A \"Clear completed\" button appears when completed todos exist — clicking shows confirmation, then deletes all completed\n- Progress text shows \"5 of 12 completed\" with a subtle progress bar\n- Filter and search state is reflected in URL query params (`?filter=active&q=milk`) and survives page refresh\n- Backend validates that due_date is a valid ISO date and priority is one of the allowed values (0-3)\n- All new fields are optional — existing tasks without them still display correctly\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use a slide-down animation for the detail panel expansion\n- Store filter/sort state in URL search params for shareability and back-button support\n- Add database migration logic — check for column existence before ALTER TABLE\n- Priority stored as integer (0-3) in the database, mapped to labels in the frontend\n- Date picker should support keyboard input as well as click selection\n- Use `Intl.RelativeTimeFormat` for relative due date display (\"due tomorrow\", \"overdue by 3 days\")\n- Use `useMemo` for derived filtered/searched todo lists\n- `<HighlightedText>` component splits text around matches and wraps matches in `<mark>`\n- Keyboard shortcuts: `/` focuses search, `Escape` clears search and resets filters\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 5: Dark Mode, Accessibility & Responsive Polish\n\n### Scope\n- Implement dark/light theme with system preference detection and manual toggle\n- Full responsive design for mobile, tablet, and desktop\n- Comprehensive keyboard navigation (Tab, arrow keys through list)\n- Screen reader support with ARIA attributes and live regions\n- Micro-interaction refinements (checkbox animation, hover effects)\n- Add keyboard shortcut help dialog (press `?` to show)\n- Focus management (trap in modals, restore after delete)\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` — Theme management with localStorage + system preference\n- `frontend/src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx` — Sun/moon toggle with transition\n- `frontend/src/styles/themes.css` — CSS custom properties for light and dark themes\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useListNavigation.ts` — Arrow key navigation for the todo list\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useKeyboardShortcuts.ts` — Global keyboard shortcut handler\n- `frontend/src/components/KeyboardShortcutHelp.tsx` — Shortcut help overlay/modal\n- `frontend/src/components/FocusTrap.tsx` — Focus trap for modals\n- Updated all components with ARIA roles, labels, and live regions\n- Responsive breakpoints applied to all layout components\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- A theme toggle (sun/moon icon) appears in the header\n- Clicking it switches between light and dark mode with a smooth 200ms color transition\n- On first load, theme matches `prefers-color-scheme` system setting\n- Theme preference persists in localStorage across page reloads\n- In dark mode, all text meets WCAG AA contrast ratio (4.5:1 minimum)\n- Dark mode feels intentional — distinct palette, not just inverted colors\n- On mobile (< 640px): single column, larger touch targets (min 44x44px), drag handle area is wider\n- On tablet (640-1024px): comfortable spacing, hover states active\n- On desktop (> 1024px): centered content with max-width ~640px\n- All interactive elements are reachable via Tab in logical order\n- Pressing Up/Down arrow keys moves focus between todo items\n- Pressing Space on a focused todo toggles completion\n- Screen reader announces each todo as \"Buy milk, incomplete\" or \"Buy milk, complete\"\n- Screen reader announces count changes via `aria-live=\"polite\"` region\n- Completing a todo plays a satisfying checkmark draw animation (not just a state change)\n- Focus returns to the next item when a todo is deleted (or previous if last)\n- Pressing `?` shows a keyboard shortcuts overlay listing all available shortcuts\n- Pressing `n` focuses the new task input\n- Pressing `j`/`k` navigates up/down the task list\n- Focus is trapped inside the shortcut help modal; Escape closes it and returns focus to trigger\n- `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` disables animations\n- Focus rings are visible on keyboard navigation but hidden on mouse interaction (`:focus-visible`)\n\n### Technical Notes\n- CSS custom properties on `:root` and `[data-theme=\"dark\"]` for all colors\n- Use `window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)')` for initial detection\n- Store theme in localStorage key `theme` with values `light`, `dark`, `system`\n- List navigation: `role=\"listbox\"` on container, `role=\"option\"` on items, `aria-activedescendant` for focus\n- Checkbox animation: CSS keyframe animation drawing a checkmark path (SVG or CSS)\n- Mobile breakpoints: 640px (mobile), 768px (tablet), 1024px (desktop)\n- Keyboard shortcuts: register on `document` with `keydown`, check `event.target` to avoid firing in inputs\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 6: IndexedDB Storage & Service Worker\n\n### Scope\n- Set up IndexedDB with Dexie.js as the local persistent store\n- Register a service worker via vite-plugin-pwa for offline asset caching\n- Make the app load and function fully without network connectivity\n- Implement a sync queue for mutations made while offline\n- Add online/offline status indicator in the UI\n- Ensure all existing features (CRUD, reorder, filter, search) work identically offline\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/db/todoDb.ts` — Dexie.js database with typed schema and CRUD operations\n- `frontend/src/db/syncQueue.ts` — Sync queue table and operations (FIFO mutation log)\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useOnlineStatus.ts` — Reactive online/offline detection hook\n- `frontend/src/components/OfflineIndicator.tsx` — Banner/badge showing connection state\n- `frontend/src/sw/` — Service worker configuration for vite-plugin-pwa\n- Updated `todoStore.ts` — reads from IndexedDB as source of truth, writes to both IndexedDB and API\n- Updated `vite.config.ts` with vite-plugin-pwa configuration\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- After first visit with network, disconnecting network (DevTools offline mode) does NOT break the app\n- Creating a todo while offline stores it in IndexedDB and shows it in the list immediately\n- Editing a todo while offline updates IndexedDB and the UI immediately\n- Deleting a todo while offline removes it from IndexedDB and the UI\n- Reordering todos while offline persists the new order in IndexedDB\n- Refreshing the page while offline loads all todos from IndexedDB (not a blank screen)\n- A subtle \"Offline\" indicator (badge or banner) appears when network is unavailable\n- The indicator changes to \"Syncing...\" when connectivity is restored\n- The indicator disappears smoothly when sync is complete\n- Filtering