            "content": "# Todo App — Build Plan\n\n## Product Vision\n\nThis is not just another todo list — it's a fast, offline-first personal task manager that feels native on any device. The app prioritizes fluid interactions: drag-and-drop reordering, inline editing, keyboard shortcuts, and instant feedback — all without requiring a network connection. When connectivity returns, changes sync seamlessly to the server.\n\nThe backend is a lightweight FastAPI service backed by SQLite, designed for single-user or small-team use without the overhead of a full database server. The API is clean, RESTful, and versioned, making it trivial to swap frontends or integrate with other tools. Every mutation is timestamped and ordered, enabling a robust offline-sync protocol built on last-write-wins with conflict detection.\n\nThe frontend is a React + TypeScript SPA bundled with Vite. It stores all data in IndexedDB via a service worker, so the app loads and operates fully offline from the first visit. The UI draws inspiration from linear.app and Things 3 — minimal chrome, generous whitespace, smooth animations, and a focus on the content itself. The result is a todo app that feels like a well-crafted native tool, not a web demo.\n\n## Technical Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                  Frontend                    │\n│  React 18 + TypeScript + Vite               │\n│  ┌───────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐ │\n│  │ UI Layer  │  │ State    │  │ Sync     │ │\n│  │ Components│◄─┤ (Zustand)│◄─┤ Engine   │ │\n│  └───────────┘  └──────────┘  └────┬─────┘ │\n│                                     │       │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐ │       │\n│  │ IndexedDB    │  │ Service      │ │       │\n│  │ (Dexie.js)  │◄─┤ Worker       │◄┘       │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘         │\n└────────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n                     │ REST API (JSON)\n┌────────────────────▼────────────────────────┐\n│                  Backend                     │\n│  FastAPI + Python 3.12+                     │\n│  ┌───────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐ │\n│  │ Routes    │  │ Service  │  │ Models   │ │\n│  │ (v1/*)    │──┤ Layer    │──┤ (SQLModel│ │\n│  └───────────┘  └──────────┘  └────┬─────┘ │\n│                                     │       │\n│                    ┌───────────────┐ │       │\n│                    │ SQLite DB     │◄┘       │\n│                    │ (aiosqlite)   │         │\n│                    └───────────────┘         │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Key technology choices:**\n- **Zustand** for state management — minimal boilerplate, immutable updates by default\n- **Dexie.js** for IndexedDB — clean Promise API, excellent TypeScript support\n- **SQLModel** (Pydantic + SQLAlchemy) for backend models — single source of truth for validation and ORM\n- **dnd-kit** for drag-and-drop — accessible, performant, framework-agnostic\n- **Workbox** for service worker — reliable offline caching with sensible defaults\n\n**Offline-sync protocol:**\n1. All mutations write to IndexedDB immediately (optimistic updates)\n2. A sync queue records each mutation with a timestamp and operation type\n3. When online, the sync engine replays the queue against the API\n4. Server responds with canonical state; client reconciles\n5. Conflicts detected via `updated_at` timestamps; last-write-wins with user notification\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 1: Project Skeleton & Backend Foundation\n\n### Scope\n- Initialize monorepo structure with frontend and backend directories\n- Set up Vite + React + TypeScript frontend with dev server\n- Set up FastAPI backend with health endpoint\n- Configure SQLite database with SQLModel\n- Implement Todo CRUD API (create, read, update, delete)\n- Add database migrations via Alembic\n- Write backend tests with pytest\n\n### Deliverables\n- `backend/` — FastAPI application with `main.py`, `models.py`, `routes/`, `services/`, `database.py`\n- `backend/alembic/` — migration configuration and initial migration\n- `backend/tests/` — pytest test suite for all CRUD endpoints\n- `backend/requirements.txt` and `backend/pyproject.toml`\n- `frontend/` — Vite + React + TypeScript scaffold with placeholder App component\n- `frontend/package.json`, `frontend/tsconfig.json`, `frontend/vite.config.ts`\n- Root `README.md` with setup instructions\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- `cd backend && pip install -r requirements.txt && uvicorn main:app` starts the server on port 8000\n- `GET /health` returns `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n- `POST /api/v1/todos` with `{\"title\": \"Buy milk\"}` returns 201 with a JSON body containing `id`, `title`, `completed`, `position`, `created_at`, `updated_at`\n- `GET /api/v1/todos` returns 200 with a JSON array of all todos\n- `GET /api/v1/todos/{id}` returns 200 with the specific todo\n- `PATCH /api/v1/todos/{id}` with `{\"title\": \"Buy oat milk\"}` returns 200 with updated todo\n- `DELETE /api/v1/todos/{id}` returns 204\n- `GET /api/v1/todos/{nonexistent_id}` returns 404 with error message\n- `POST /api/v1/todos` with empty body returns 422 with validation error\n- `cd backend && pytest` passes with 80%+ coverage\n- `cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev` starts Vite dev server\n- Frontend renders a heading \"Todo App\" on `localhost:5173`\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use SQLModel for both Pydantic validation and SQLAlchemy ORM in one class\n- Use `aiosqlite` for async SQLite access\n- Each todo has fields: `id` (UUID), `title` (str), `description` (optional str), `completed` (bool), `position` (float), `created_at` (datetime), `updated_at` (datetime)\n- Use float-based positioning (midpoint insertion) for O(1) reordering\n- Add CORS middleware configured for `localhost:5173`\n- Structure backend with repository pattern: routes → services → repository → database\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 2: Frontend Core — Todo List UI\n\n### Scope\n- Build the main todo list view with add, display, and complete functionality\n- Connect frontend to backend API\n- Implement inline add-todo input\n- Implement todo completion toggle with animation\n- Add empty state illustration\n- Set up Zustand store for todo state management\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/stores/todoStore.ts` — Zustand store with todos state and actions\n- `frontend/src/api/todoApi.ts` — API client with typed fetch wrappers\n- `frontend/src/components/TodoList.tsx` — main list component\n- `frontend/src/components/TodoItem.tsx` — individual todo row with checkbox\n- `frontend/src/components/AddTodo.tsx` — inline input for adding todos\n- `frontend/src/components/EmptyState.tsx` — friendly empty state\n- `frontend/src/styles/` — CSS modules or Tailwind classes for all components\n- `frontend/src/types/todo.ts` — shared TypeScript types\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- App loads and displays todos fetched from the backend API\n- Typing in the input field and pressing Enter creates a new todo that appears in the list without page reload\n- Pressing Enter with an empty input does nothing (no empty todos created)\n- Clicking the checkbox on a todo toggles its `completed` state, visually striking through the title\n- Completed todos show a smooth strikethrough animation (CSS transition, not instant)\n- When no todos exist, an empty state message is displayed: \"No todos yet. Add one above!\"\n- The add-todo input auto-focuses on page load\n- All API calls show a loading indicator while in progress\n- If the backend is unreachable, an error banner appears at the top of the page\n- Todo titles longer than 200 characters are rejected with a client-side validation message\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use Zustand with immer middleware for immutable state updates\n- API client should use a base URL from environment variable `VITE_API_URL` (default `http://localhost:8000`)\n- Use React Query or SWR for server state if preferred, but Zustand is sufficient\n- CSS: use Tailwind CSS for utility-first styling — install via Vite plugin\n- Keep components small; TodoItem should be < 80 lines\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 3: Inline Editing & Delete\n\n### Scope\n- Add inline editing — double-click or press Enter on a todo to edit its title in place\n- Add delete functionality with confirmation\n- Add description field (expandable detail view)\n- Add keyboard shortcuts for common actions\n\n### Deliverables\n- Updated `TodoItem.tsx` with inline edit mode (input replaces text on activation)\n- `frontend/src/components/TodoDetail.tsx` — expandable description panel\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useKeyboardShortcuts.ts` — keyboard shortcut handler\n- Delete button/icon on each todo with confirmation dialog\n- Updated backend: ensure PATCH supports partial updates for `title`, `description`, `completed`\n- Updated Zustand store with edit and delete actions\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Double-clicking a todo title enters edit mode: the title text becomes an input field pre-filled with the current title\n- Pressing Enter in edit mode saves the change and exits edit mode\n- Pressing Escape in edit mode discards changes and exits edit mode\n- Clicking outside the input while in edit mode saves the change\n- An empty title is rejected — the input shows a red border and \"Title cannot be empty\" message\n- Each todo has a delete button (trash icon) that appears on hover\n- Clicking delete shows a confirmation dialog; confirming removes the todo with a fade-out animation\n- Pressing `n` when not in an input focuses the add-todo input\n- Pressing `d` with a todo focused/selected shows the description panel\n- Pressing `Backspace` or `Delete` with a todo selected triggers the delete confirmation\n- The description panel expands below the todo item with a smooth slide-down animation\n- Description supports multi-line text (textarea, not input)\n- Description changes are saved on blur or Ctrl+Enter\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use `contentEditable` or a controlled input for inline editing — controlled input is safer\n- Keyboard shortcuts should only fire when no input/textarea is focused (except specific ones)\n- Use `framer-motion` or CSS transitions for animations\n- Confirmation dialog should be a custom modal component, not `window.confirm()`\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 4: Drag-and-Drop Reordering\n\n### Scope\n- Implement drag-and-drop reordering of todos\n- Persist order to backend\n- Add visual drag feedback (ghost element, drop indicators)\n- Handle position recalculation to avoid float precision issues\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/components/SortableTodoList.tsx` — dnd-kit powered sortable list\n- `frontend/src/components/DragHandle.tsx` — grip icon for drag initiation\n- Updated backend: `PATCH /api/v1/todos/{id}/reorder` endpoint accepting `{\"position\": float}`\n- Backend: position normalization endpoint/logic for when positions get too close\n- Updated Zustand store with optimistic reorder logic\n- CSS for drag states: ghost opacity, drop zone highlight, smooth layout shift\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Each todo displays a drag handle (grip icon) on the left side\n- Grabbing the drag handle and dragging a todo vertically reorders the list in real time\n- A semi-transparent ghost of the dragged item follows the cursor\n- A colored line indicator shows where the item will be dropped\n- Releasing the item places it in the indicated position\n- The new order persists after page refresh (verified by refreshing and checking order)\n- Dragging the first item to the last position works correctly\n- Dragging the last item to the first position works correctly\n- Reordering 3+ items in sequence without refresh maintains correct order each time\n- On mobile viewports (< 768px), touch-based drag and drop works\n- Backend: `PATCH /api/v1/todos/{id}/reorder` with `{\"after_id\": \"<uuid>\"}` returns 200 with updated position\n- If positions become too dense (difference < 0.0001), the backend normalizes all positions to evenly spaced integers\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use `@dnd-kit/core` and `@dnd-kit/sortable` for drag-and-drop\n- Position calculation: new position = midpoint between neighbors. If inserting at start, use `first_position - 1.0`; at end, use `last_position + 1.0`\n- Implement position normalization: when min gap < threshold, reassign all positions as 1.0, 2.0, 3.0, ...\n- Use `useSensors` with both pointer and keyboard sensors for accessibility\n- Optimistic update: reorder locally immediately, then sync to backend; revert on error\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 5: Filtering, Search & Bulk Actions\n\n### Scope\n- Add filter tabs: All, Active, Completed\n- Add search/filter input for finding todos by title\n- Add bulk actions: mark all complete, delete completed\n- Add todo count badges\n- Add sorting options (by date, alphabetical, manual)\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/components/FilterBar.tsx` — filter tabs and search input\n- `frontend/src/components/BulkActions.tsx` — bulk action buttons\n- Updated Zustand store with filter/search state and derived selectors\n- Backend: `GET /api/v1/todos?status=active|completed&search=term&sort=position|created_at|title`\n- Backend: `POST /api/v1/todos/bulk` for bulk operations\n- `frontend/src/components/TodoCount.tsx` — shows \"3 of 7 items\" style count\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Three filter tabs appear above the list: \"All\", \"Active\", \"Completed\"\n- Clicking \"Active\" shows only todos where `completed === false`\n- Clicking \"Completed\" shows only todos where `completed === true`\n- The active filter tab is visually highlighted (different background/underline)\n- A search input filters todos by title as the user types (debounced, 300ms)\n- Search is case-insensitive: searching \"buy\" matches \"Buy Milk\"\n- Search with no results shows \"No todos match your search\" message\n- A \"Mark all complete\" button appears when there are active todos; clicking it completes all visible todos\n- A \"Clear completed\" button appears when there are completed todos; clicking it deletes all completed todos with a confirmation dialog\n- The count display shows \"X items left\" where X is the number of active (incomplete) todos\n- Sort dropdown with options: \"Manual\" (drag order), \"Newest first\", \"Oldest first\", \"A-Z\"\n- Changing sort order immediately reorders the list with a subtle animation\n- Keyboard shortcut `/` focuses the search input\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Filter and search should work client-side for instant feedback, with backend query params for fresh loads\n- Use `useMemo` for derived/filtered todo lists to avoid unnecessary re-renders\n- Debounce search input with a custom `useDebounce` hook\n- Bulk operations should use a single API call, not N individual calls\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 6: Polish — Animations, Theme & Responsive Design\n\n### Scope\n- Add dark/light theme toggle with system preference detection\n- Responsive design for mobile, tablet, desktop\n- Micro-animations for all interactions (add, delete, complete, reorder)\n- Accessibility audit and fixes (ARIA labels, focus management, screen reader support)\n- Keyboard navigation for the entire app (arrow keys to navigate list)\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` — theme management with localStorage persistence\n- `frontend/src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx` — sun/moon toggle button\n- `frontend/src/styles/theme.css` — CSS custom properties for both themes\n- Updated all components with responsive breakpoints\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useListNavigation.ts` — arrow key navigation for todo list\n- ARIA attributes on all interactive elements\n- `frontend/src/components/SkipLink.tsx` — skip-to-content link for accessibility\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- A theme toggle button (sun/moon icon) appears in the header\n- Clicking it switches between light and dark themes with a smooth color transition (200ms)\n- On first load, the theme matches the system preference (`prefers-color-scheme`)\n- Theme choice persists in localStorage across page reloads\n- On mobile (< 640px): single column layout, larger touch targets (min 44x44px), no hover states\n- On tablet (640-1024px): comfortable spacing, hover states active\n- On desktop (> 1024px): centered content with max-width, comfortable reading width\n- All interactive elements have visible focus rings when navigating with keyboard\n- Pressing Up/Down arrow keys moves focus between todo items in the list\n- Pressing Space on a focused todo toggles its completion\n- Screen reader announces \"Todo: Buy milk, incomplete\" (or \"complete\") for each item\n- All color combinations meet WCAG 2.1 AA contrast ratio (4.5:1 for text)\n- Adding a todo plays a subtle slide-in animation\n- Deleting a todo plays a fade-out + collapse animation\n- Completing a todo plays a satisfying checkmark animation\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use CSS custom properties (variables) for theming — swap a single class on `<html>`\n- Use `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` for initial theme detection\n- Test with browser DevTools responsive mode and screen reader (VoiceOver on macOS)\n- Use `framer-motion` `AnimatePresence` for enter/exit animations on list items\n- Focus management: when a todo is deleted, focus moves to the next item (or previous if last)\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 7: Offline Mode — IndexedDB & Service Worker\n\n### Scope\n- Implement IndexedDB storage with Dexie.js as the primary local data store\n- Register a service worker (Workbox) for offline asset caching\n- Make the app fully functional without network connectivity\n- Add online/offline status indicator\n- Implement sync queue for mutations made while offline\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/db/todoDb.ts` — Dexie.js database schema and operations\n- `frontend/src/sw.ts` — service worker with Workbox precaching and runtime caching\n- `frontend/src/sync/syncQueue.ts` — queue for offline mutations\n- `frontend/src/sync/syncEngine.ts` — reconciliation engine\n- `frontend/src/components/OfflineIndicator.tsx` — online/offline status banner\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useOnlineStatus.ts` — reactive online status hook\n- Updated Zustand store: reads from IndexedDB, writes to both IndexedDB and sync queue\n- `frontend/vite.config.ts` updated with `vite-plugin-pwa` for service worker generation\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- After first visit with network, the app loads and functions fully when the network is disconnected (airplane mode / DevTools offline)\n- Creating a todo while offline stores it in IndexedDB and shows it in the list immediately\n- Editing a todo while offline updates IndexedDB and the UI immediately\n- Deleting a todo while offline removes it from IndexedDB and the UI immediately\n- Reordering todos while offline persists the new order in IndexedDB\n- An \"Offline\" banner/badge appears when the network is disconnected\n- When the network reconnects, the banner changes to \"Syncing...\" then disappears\n- After reconnecting, all offline changes are synced to the backend (verified by checking the backend API directly)\n- If the same todo was edited on both client (offline) and server, the most recent edit wins (by `updated_at` timestamp)\n- The app works after closing and reopening the browser tab while offline\n- `navigator.serviceWorker.ready` resolves successfully after first load\n- IndexedDB contains a `todos` table and a `syncQueue` table\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use `vite-plugin-pwa` with `generateSW` strategy for Workbox integration\n- Dexie.js schema: `db.version(1).stores({ todos: 'id, position, updated_at', syncQueue: '++id, operation, todoId, timestamp' })`\n- Sync queue operations: `CREATE`, `UPDATE`, `DELETE`, `REORDER` — each with full payload\n- On reconnect: replay sync queue in order; for each operation, compare `updated_at` with server version\n- Use `navigator.onLine` + `window.addEventListener('online'/'offline')` for connectivity detection\n- Service worker should cache: app shell (HTML, JS, CSS), API responses (stale-while-revalidate for GET)\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 8: Sync Robustness & Conflict Resolution\n\n### Scope\n- Harden the sync protocol with retry logic and exponential backoff\n- Implement conflict detection and resolution UI\n- Add sync status per todo (synced, pending, conflict)\n- Handle edge cases: duplicate creates, out-of-order operations, server errors\n- Add data export/import (JSON)\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/sync/retryQueue.ts` — retry logic with exponential backoff\n- `frontend/src/sync/conflictResolver.ts` — conflict detection and resolution\n- `frontend/src/components/SyncStatus.tsx` — per-todo sync indicator (cloud icon states)\n- `frontend/src/components/ConflictDialog.tsx` — conflict resolution modal\n- `frontend/src/components/DataExport.tsx` — export/import buttons\n- Backend: `GET /api/v1/todos/export` and `POST /api/v1/todos/import` endpoints\n- Backend: `GET /api/v1/todos/changes?since=<timestamp>` for incremental sync\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Each todo shows a small sync icon: ✓ (synced/green), ↻ (pending/yellow), ⚠ (conflict/red)\n- When a sync request fails, it retries with exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, max 30s)\n- After 5 failed retries, the todo shows a \"Sync failed\" status with a manual \"Retry\" button\n- If the same todo is edited offline on two different tabs/devices, a conflict dialog appears showing both versions with \"Keep mine\", \"Keep theirs\", and \"Keep both\" options\n- Clicking \"Export\" downloads a `todos-YYYY-MM-DD.json` file containing all todos\n- Clicking \"Import\" opens a file picker; selecting a valid JSON file imports the todos\n- Importing a JSON file with invalid format shows an error: \"Invalid file format\"\n- `GET /api/v1/todos/changes?since=2024-01-01T00:00:00Z` returns only todos modified after that timestamp\n- The sync engine processes the queue in FIFO order; a failed item blocks subsequent items for the same todo (but not other todos)\n- Network errors during sync do not corrupt local IndexedDB data\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Exponential backoff: `delay = min(baseDelay * 2^attempt, maxDelay)` with jitter\n- Conflict detection: compare `updated_at` from sync response with local `updated_at`; if server is newer and local has pending changes, it's a conflict\n- Per-todo sync status stored in Zustand, not IndexedDB (ephemeral UI state)\n- Export format: `{ \"version\": 1, \"exported_at\": \"...\", \"todos\": [...] }`\n- Import should merge, not replace (skip todos with matching IDs unless imported version is newer)\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 9: Backend Hardening & Production Readiness\n\n### Scope\n- Add rate limiting to all API endpoints\n- Add request validation and sanitization\n- Add structured logging with request tracing\n- Add API documentation (auto-generated OpenAPI + custom docs)\n- Add database backup/restore functionality\n- Performance optimization (indexes, query optimization, response compression)\n- Add health check with dependency status\n\n### Deliverables\n- `backend/middleware/rate_limit.py` — sliding window rate limiter\n- `backend/middleware/logging.py` — structured JSON logging with request IDs\n- `backend/middleware/security.py` — input sanitization, security headers\n- Updated `database.py` with proper indexes and connection pooling\n- `backend/scripts/backup.py` — SQLite backup utility\n- Updated OpenAPI docs with examples and descriptions\n- `backend/tests/test_rate_limit.py`, `backend/tests/test_security.py`\n- Comprehensive API error responses with consistent error format\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- API endpoints return rate limit headers: `X-RateLimit-Limit`, `X-RateLimit-Remaining`, `X-RateLimit-Reset`\n- Exceeding 100 requests/minute to any endpoint returns 429 with `{\"error\": \"Rate limit exceeded\", \"retry_after\": N}`\n- All API responses include `X-Request-Id` header for tracing\n- Server logs are structured JSON with fields: `timestamp`, `level`, `request_id`, `method`, `path`, `status`, `duration_ms`\n- `GET /health` returns `{\"status\": \"ok\", \"database\": \"connected\", \"version\": \"1.0.0\"}`\n- `GET /docs` serves interactive Swagger UI with all endpoints documented\n- HTML/script tags in todo titles are stripped (not stored): `<script>alert('xss')</script>` becomes `alert('xss')`\n- `python scripts/backup.py` creates a timestamped backup file in `backups/`\n- All API error responses follow the format: `{\"error\": {\"code\": \"NOT_FOUND\", \"message\": \"Todo not found\", \"details\": {}}}`\n- Backend test suite passes with 85%+ coverage\n- SQLite database has indexes on `todos.position` and `todos.updated_at`\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use `slowapi` for rate limiting (built on `limits` library)\n- Use `python-json-logger` for structured logging\n- Security headers: `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block`\n- Input sanitization: strip HTML tags using `bleach` library, limit title to 200 chars, description to 5000 chars\n- SQLite backup: use `sqlite3.backup()` API for online backup without locking\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 10: End-to-End Testing & Final Integration\n\n### Scope\n- Write comprehensive E2E tests covering all user flows\n- Cross-browser testing (Chrome, Firefox, Safari)\n- Performance audit (Lighthouse)\n- Final integration testing: offline → online sync flow\n- Build production bundles and verify deployment readiness\n- Write user documentation\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/e2e/` — Playwright test suite with tests for all major flows\n- `frontend/e2e/todo-crud.spec.ts` — create, read, update, delete flows\n- `frontend/e2e/drag-and-drop.spec.ts` — reordering tests\n- `frontend/e2e/offline-sync.spec.ts` — offline mode and sync tests\n- `frontend/e2e/accessibility.spec.ts` — axe-core accessibility audit\n- `frontend/lighthouse/` — Lighthouse CI configuration and baseline scores\n- Production build scripts in `package.json`\n- `docs/USER_GUIDE.md` — end-user documentation with screenshots\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- `cd frontend && npx playwright test` runs all E2E tests