            "content": "# Todo App — Build Plan\n\n## Product Vision\n\nThis is not just another todo list — it's a fast, offline-first personal task manager that feels native on the web. Users should be able to capture, organize, and complete tasks with zero friction, whether they're online, offline, or transitioning between states. The app prioritizes speed of interaction: adding a task should feel instant, reordering should be buttery smooth via drag-and-drop, and edits should happen inline without modal interruptions.\n\nThe architecture splits cleanly between a React + TypeScript frontend (bundled with Vite) and a FastAPI + SQLite backend. SQLite gives us a zero-config, file-based database that's perfect for single-user or small-team scenarios, while FastAPI provides async performance and automatic OpenAPI documentation. The offline-first design means the frontend maintains its own local state (via IndexedDB) and syncs with the backend opportunistically — the app is fully functional without a network connection.\n\nBeyond the basics, this app should demonstrate craft: thoughtful animations on reorder, keyboard-driven workflows, clear visual hierarchy, and a design that feels intentional rather than generic. Drawing inspiration from Things 3 and Linear, the UI uses generous whitespace, subtle depth cues, and satisfying micro-interactions. Accessibility, error recovery, and data integrity during sync conflicts are first-class concerns, not afterthoughts.\n\n## Technical Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                   Frontend                       │\n│  React 18 + TypeScript + Vite                    │\n│                                                  │\n│  ┌───────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐ │\n│  │ Components │  │ State Mgmt │  │  Sync Layer │ │\n│  │ (UI)       │  │ (Zustand)  │  │ (Service    │ │\n│  │            │  │            │  │  Worker)    │ │\n│  └───────────┘  └────────────┘  └─────────────┘ │\n│        │              │               │          │\n│        └──────────────┼───────────────┘          │\n│                       │                          │\n│              ┌────────┴────────┐                 │\n│              │   IndexedDB     │                 │\n│              │  (Dexie.js)     │                 │\n│              └─────────────────┘                 │\n└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────┘\n                        │ HTTP/REST (when online)\n┌───────────────────────┴─────────────────────────┐\n│                   Backend                        │\n│  FastAPI + Python 3.12+                          │\n│                                                  │\n│  ┌───────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐ │\n│  │  Routes   │  │  Services  │  │ Repository  │ │\n│  │ (API)     │  │ (Business) │  │ (Data)      │ │\n│  └───────────┘  └────────────┘  └─────────────┘ │\n│                                       │          │\n│                              ┌────────┴────────┐ │\n│                              │     SQLite      │ │\n│                              │  (aiosqlite)    │ │\n│                              └─────────────────┘ │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Key technology choices:**\n\n- **Zustand** for state management — minimal boilerplate, immutable updates via immer middleware\n- **Dexie.js** for IndexedDB — clean Promise API, excellent TypeScript support\n- **aiosqlite** for async SQLite access in FastAPI\n- **Pydantic v2** for request/response validation on the backend\n- **@dnd-kit** for drag-and-drop — accessible, performant, framework-agnostic\n- **Workbox** (via vite-plugin-pwa) for service worker — reliable offline caching\n- **Tailwind CSS** for utility-first styling with custom design tokens\n- **framer-motion** for animations — AnimatePresence for enter/exit, layout animations for reorder\n\n**Offline-sync protocol:**\n1. All mutations write to IndexedDB immediately (optimistic updates)\n2. A sync queue records each mutation with a timestamp and operation type\n3. When online, the sync engine replays the queue against the API\n4. Server responds with canonical state; client reconciles\n5. Conflicts detected via `updated_at` timestamps; last-write-wins with user notification\n\n**Data model:**\n- `id`: UUID (generated client-side for offline creates)\n- `title`: string (1-200 chars, required)\n- `completed`: boolean (default false)\n- `position`: float (midpoint insertion for O(1) reorder)\n- `created_at`: ISO 8601 datetime\n- `updated_at`: ISO 8601 datetime\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 1: Project Skeleton & Backend CRUD API\n\n### Scope\n- Initialize monorepo structure with frontend and backend directories\n- Set up Vite + React + TypeScript frontend with Tailwind CSS\n- Set up FastAPI backend with SQLite database and health endpoint\n- Define the Todo data model with Pydantic schemas\n- Implement full CRUD API with proper validation and error handling\n- Implement reorder endpoint for position updates\n- Write comprehensive backend tests with pytest\n- Configure CORS and dev server proxying\n\n### Deliverables\n- `backend/main.py` — FastAPI application entry point with CORS middleware\n- `backend/database.py` — async SQLite connection management with aiosqlite\n- `backend/models.py` — SQLite table definitions\n- `backend/schemas.py` — Pydantic v2 request/response models\n- `backend/repository.py` — TodoRepository with all DB operations\n- `backend/services.py` — Business logic layer\n- `backend/routes/todos.py` — REST API endpoints\n- `backend/tests/test_todos.py` — pytest test suite for all endpoints\n- `backend/requirements.txt` — Python dependencies\n- `frontend/` — Vite + React + TypeScript scaffold with Tailwind CSS configured\n- `frontend/package.json`, `frontend/tsconfig.json`, `frontend/vite.config.ts`\n- Root `README.md` with setup and run instructions\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Running `cd backend && pip install -r requirements.txt && python -m uvicorn main:app` starts the server on port 8000\n- `GET /health` returns 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\"}`\n- `POST /api/todos` with `{\"title\": \"Buy milk\"}` returns 201 with JSON body containing `id`, `title`, `completed`, `position`, `created_at`, `updated_at`\n- `GET /api/todos` returns 200 with a JSON array of all todos sorted by `position` ascending\n- `GET /api/todos/{id}` returns 200 with the specific todo, or 404 with `{\"detail\": \"Todo not found\"}`\n- `PUT /api/todos/{id}` with `{\"title\": \"Buy oat milk\", \"completed\": true}` returns 200 with the updated todo\n- `DELETE /api/todos/{id}` returns 204 and the todo is no longer returned by GET\n- `PATCH /api/todos/{id}/reorder` with `{\"position\": 2.5}` returns 200 with updated position\n- `POST /api/todos` with `{\"title\": \"\"}` returns 422 with validation error\n- `POST /api/todos` with `{\"title\": \"x\" * 201}` returns 422 with validation error\n- Running `cd backend && python -m pytest` passes with 80%+ coverage\n- Running `cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev` starts Vite dev server on port 5173\n- Frontend renders a heading \"Todo App\" at `http://localhost:5173`\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use `aiosqlite` for async SQLite — do NOT use SQLAlchemy or SQLModel (keep it lightweight)\n- Repository pattern: routes → services → repository → database\n- Use float-based positioning: when inserting between items at positions 2.0 and 3.0, new position = 2.5\n- CORS: allow `http://localhost:5173` in development\n- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` with `TestClient` for API tests\n- Pydantic v2 models: `TodoCreate`, `TodoUpdate`, `TodoResponse`, `TodoReorder`\n- Database schema: create table in `database.py` on startup (no migration framework needed for SQLite)\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 2: Core Frontend UI & API Integration\n\n### Scope\n- Build the main todo list view with add, display, complete, and delete\n- Connect frontend to backend API with a typed fetch-based client\n- Implement Zustand store for todo state management\n- Add loading states, error handling, and empty states\n- Establish the visual design system (colors, typography, spacing, shadows)\n- Add inline editing (double-click to edit, Enter to save, Escape to cancel)\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/types/todo.ts` — TypeScript types matching backend schemas\n- `frontend/src/api/todoApi.ts` — Typed API client with error handling\n- `frontend/src/store/todoStore.ts` — Zustand store with immer middleware\n- `frontend/src/components/TodoList.tsx` — Main list container\n- `frontend/src/components/TodoItem.tsx` — Individual todo with checkbox, edit, delete\n- `frontend/src/components/AddTodo.tsx` — Input for creating new todos\n- `frontend/src/components/EmptyState.tsx` — Friendly empty state message\n- `frontend/src/components/ErrorBanner.tsx` — Error notification banner\n- `frontend/src/components/LoadingSpinner.tsx` — Loading indicator\n- Tailwind CSS configuration with custom color palette and design tokens\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- App loads and displays todos fetched from the backend API\n- User can type a todo title and press Enter to add it — the todo appears in the list immediately\n- Pressing Enter with an empty input does nothing (no empty todos)\n- User can click the checkbox to toggle completed state — completed todos show strikethrough with a CSS transition\n- User can double-click a todo title to enter inline edit mode — title becomes an editable input\n- Pressing Enter in edit mode saves the change; pressing Escape cancels and reverts\n- Clicking outside the edit input saves the change (blur handler)\n- An empty title in edit mode is rejected with a red border and validation message\n- Each todo has a delete button (trash icon) visible on hover — clicking it removes the todo\n- When no todos exist, a friendly empty state is shown with the message \"No todos yet\"\n- While data loads from the API, a spinner or skeleton is shown\n- If the API is unreachable, an error banner appears with a descriptive message\n- The UI has clear visual hierarchy: header area, input area, list area with proper spacing\n- Todo titles longer than 200 characters are rejected with client-side validation\n- All interactive elements have visible hover and focus states\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Zustand store with immer middleware for immutable updates\n- API client: thin fetch wrapper with base URL from `VITE_API_URL` env var (default `http://localhost:8000`)\n- Use `React.memo` on `TodoItem` to prevent unnecessary re-renders\n- Tailwind CSS: configure custom colors, fonts, and spacing in `tailwind.config.ts`\n- Keep components focused: TodoItem should be < 100 lines\n- Error handling: catch network errors and display user-friendly messages, never raw error objects\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 3: Drag-and-Drop Reordering & Animations\n\n### Scope\n- Implement smooth drag-and-drop reordering using @dnd-kit\n- Add visual feedback during drag (placeholder, shadow, elevation)\n- Persist new order to backend via the reorder API\n- Add keyboard-accessible reordering (Alt+Up / Alt+Down)\n- Add framer-motion animations for add, remove, and reorder transitions\n- Add a drag handle component\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/components/SortableTodoList.tsx` — dnd-kit powered sortable list\n- `frontend/src/components/SortableTodoItem.tsx` — Sortable wrapper for TodoItem\n- `frontend/src/components/DragHandle.tsx` — Visual grip handle for initiating drag\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useTodoReorder.ts` — Hook encapsulating reorder logic\n- Updated `todoStore.ts` with optimistic reorder and rollback\n- Updated `todoApi.ts` with batch reorder support\n- `backend/routes/todos.py` — New `PUT /api/todos/reorder` batch endpoint\n- Animation integration with framer-motion across all list mutations\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Each todo displays a drag handle (grip dots icon) on the left side\n- Grabbing the drag handle and dragging vertically reorders the list in real time\n- The dragged item has a subtle shadow/elevation effect and slight scale increase while being dragged\n- A colored line indicator shows where the item will be dropped\n- After dropping, the new order persists across page refreshes (saved to backend)\n- User can focus a todo and press Alt+Up or Alt+Down to move it up/down — the item animates to its new position\n- Adding a new todo plays a slide-in animation from the top\n- Deleting a todo plays a fade-out + collapse animation\n- Reordering plays a smooth layout shift animation (no teleporting)\n- Dragging the first item to the last position works correctly\n- Dragging the last item to the first position works correctly\n- The batch reorder endpoint `PUT /api/todos/reorder` accepts `[{\"id\": \"...\", \"position\": 1.0}, ...]` and updates all atomically\n- Reordering 20+ items feels smooth with no visible jank\n- Screen readers announce position changes: \"Task moved to position 3 of 7\"\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use `@dnd-kit/core` and `@dnd-kit/sortable` with both PointerSensor and KeyboardSensor\n- Optimistic updates: reorder local state immediately, sync to server, revert on failure with toast notification\n- Use `framer-motion` `<AnimatePresence>` for exit animations and `layout` prop for reorder animations\n- Batch reorder: send full position list after drag ends (more reliable than single-item updates)\n- Position recalculation: after reorder, assign sequential positions (1.0, 2.0, 3.0...) to avoid float precision drift\n- ARIA: use `aria-roledescription=\"sortable\"` and announce position changes via live region\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 4: Filtering, Search & Keyboard Shortcuts\n\n### Scope\n- Add filter tabs: All, Active, Completed with count badges\n- Implement instant search with highlighted matches\n- Add bulk actions: mark all complete, clear completed\n- Add progress visualization (completed count)\n- Implement keyboard shortcuts for power users\n- Add keyboard shortcut help dialog\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/components/FilterBar.tsx` — Filter tabs with count badges\n- `frontend/src/components/SearchInput.tsx` — Search input with debounced filtering\n- `frontend/src/components/BulkActions.tsx` — Bulk action toolbar\n- `frontend/src/components/ProgressIndicator.tsx` — Visual progress (e.g., \"5 of 12 done\")\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useKeyboardShortcuts.ts` — Global keyboard shortcut handler\n- `frontend/src/components/KeyboardShortcutHelp.tsx` — Help modal listing shortcuts\n- `frontend/src/components/HighlightedText.tsx` — Text with search match highlighting\n- Updated store with filter, search state, and derived selectors\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Three filter tabs appear above the list: \"All (7)\", \"Active (5)\", \"Completed (2)\" with live counts\n- Clicking \"Active\" shows only incomplete todos; \"Completed\" shows only completed todos\n- The active filter tab has a distinct visual style (underline or background highlight)\n- A search input filters todos by title as the user types (debounced 200ms)\n- Search is case-insensitive: \"buy\" matches \"Buy Milk\"\n- Matching text is highlighted with a `<mark>` element in search results\n- Search with no results shows \"No todos match your search\"\n- A \"Mark all complete\" checkbox in the header toggles all todos\n- A \"Clear completed\" button appears when completed todos exist — clicking shows confirmation, then deletes all completed\n- Progress text shows \"5 of 12 completed\" with a subtle progress bar\n- Keyboard shortcut `n` focuses the add-todo input (when not already in an input)\n- Keyboard shortcut `/` focuses the search input\n- Keyboard shortcut `?` opens the shortcut help modal\n- Keyboard shortcut `Escape` clears search and resets filters\n- The shortcut help modal is dismissible with Escape or clicking outside\n- All filters and search work entirely client-side (no API calls for filtering)\n- Filter state is reflected in the URL query params (`?filter=active&q=milk`) and survives page refresh\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use `useMemo` for derived filtered/searched todo lists\n- Debounce with `useDeferredValue` or custom `useDebounce` hook\n- `<HighlightedText>` component splits text around matches and wraps matches in `<mark>`\n- URL sync: use `URLSearchParams` to read/write filter and search state\n- Keyboard shortcuts: register on `document` with `keydown`, check `event.target` to avoid firing in inputs\n- Bulk operations: call individual API endpoints but batch the state updates\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 5: Dark Mode, Accessibility & Responsive Polish\n\n### Scope\n- Implement dark/light theme with system preference detection and manual toggle\n- Full responsive design for mobile, tablet, and desktop\n- Comprehensive keyboard navigation (Tab, arrow keys through list)\n- Screen reader support with ARIA attributes and live regions\n- Micro-interaction refinements (checkbox animation, hover effects)\n- Focus management (trap in modals, restore after delete)\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` — Theme management with localStorage + system preference\n- `frontend/src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx` — Sun/moon toggle with transition\n- `frontend/src/styles/themes.css` — CSS custom properties for light and dark themes\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useListNavigation.ts` — Arrow key navigation for the todo list\n- `frontend/src/components/FocusTrap.tsx` — Focus trap for modals\n- Updated all components with ARIA roles, labels, and live regions\n- Responsive breakpoints applied to all layout components\n- Refined animations on checkbox toggle, hover states, and transitions\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- A theme toggle (sun/moon icon) appears in the header\n- Clicking it switches between light and dark mode with a smooth 200ms color transition\n- On first load, theme matches `prefers-color-scheme` system setting\n- Theme preference persists in localStorage across page reloads\n- In dark mode, all text meets WCAG AA contrast ratio (4.5:1 minimum)\n- Dark mode feels intentional — distinct palette, not just inverted colors\n- On mobile (< 640px): single column, larger touch targets (min 44x44px), drag handle area is wider\n- On tablet (640-1024px): comfortable spacing, hover states active\n- On desktop (> 1024px): centered content with max-width ~640px\n- All interactive elements are reachable via Tab in logical order\n- Pressing Up/Down arrow keys moves focus between todo items\n- Pressing Space on a focused todo toggles completion\n- Screen reader announces each todo as \"Buy milk, incomplete\" or \"Buy milk, complete\"\n- Screen reader announces count changes via `aria-live=\"polite\"` region\n- Completing a todo plays a satisfying checkmark draw animation (not just a state change)\n- Focus returns to the next item when a todo is deleted (or previous if last)\n- Focus is trapped inside the shortcut help modal; Escape closes it and returns focus to trigger\n\n### Technical Notes\n- CSS custom properties on `:root` and `[data-theme=\"dark\"]` for all colors\n- Use `window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)')` for initial detection\n- Store theme in localStorage key `theme` with values `light`, `dark`, `system`\n- List navigation: `role=\"listbox\"` on container, `role=\"option\"` on items, `aria-activedescendant` for focus\n- Test with VoiceOver (macOS) and axe DevTools browser extension\n- Checkbox animation: CSS keyframe animation drawing a checkmark path (SVG or CSS)\n- `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` — disable animations for users who prefer reduced motion\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 6: IndexedDB Storage & Service Worker\n\n### Scope\n- Set up IndexedDB with Dexie.js as the local persistent store\n- Register a service worker via vite-plugin-pwa for offline asset caching\n- Make the app load and function fully without network connectivity\n- Implement a sync queue for mutations made while offline\n- Add online/offline status indicator in the UI\n- Ensure all existing features work identically offline\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/db/todoDb.ts` — Dexie.js database with typed schema and CRUD operations\n- `frontend/src/db/syncQueue.ts` — Sync queue table and operations (FIFO mutation log)\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useOnlineStatus.ts` — Reactive online/offline detection hook\n- `frontend/src/components/OfflineIndicator.tsx` — Banner/badge showing connection state\n- `frontend/src/sw/` — Service worker configuration for vite-plugin-pwa\n- Updated `todoStore.ts` — reads from IndexedDB as source of truth, writes to both IndexedDB and API\n- Updated `vite.config.ts` with vite-plugin-pwa configuration\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- After first visit with network, disconnecting network (DevTools offline mode) does NOT break the app\n- Creating a todo while offline stores it in IndexedDB and shows it in the list immediately\n- Editing a todo while offline updates IndexedDB and the UI immediately\n- Deleting a todo while offline removes it from IndexedDB and the UI\n- Reordering todos while offline persists the new order in IndexedDB\n- Refreshing the page while offline loads all todos from IndexedDB (not a blank screen)\n- A subtle \"Offline\" indicator (badge or banner) appears when network is unavailable\n- The indicator disappears smoothly when connection is restored\n- Filtering, searching, and bulk actions all work offline (they operate on IndexedDB data)\n- The service worker caches the app shell (HTML, JS, CSS) — repeat visits load instantly even offline\n- IndexedDB contains a `todos` object store and a `syncQueue` object store (verifiable in DevTools)\n- Sync queue entries have structure: `{id, type: 'create'|'update'|'delete'|'reorder', payload, timestamp}`\n- Opening the app for the first time with no cached data and no network shows a clear \"Connect to get started\" message\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Dexie schema: `db.version(1).stores({ todos: 'id, position, updatedAt', syncQueue: '++id, type, todoId, timestamp' })`\n- vite-plugin-pwa with `generateSW` strategy and Workbox runtime caching\n- Service worker strategies: Cache-First for static assets, Network-First for API GET requests\n- Online detection: combine `navigator.onLine` with `online`/`offline` events; optionally ping `/health`\n- Store reads: always read from IndexedDB first (source of truth for UI), hydrate from API when online\n- Temporary IDs: generate UUID v4 client-side for todos created offline; these get replaced after sync\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 7: Background Sync & Conflict Resolution\n\n### Scope\n- Implement background sync engine that replays the mutation queue on reconnect\n- Handle sync conflicts with last-write-wins strategy\n- Add retry logic with exponential backoff for failed syncs\n- Show sync status in the UI (synced, syncing, pending, error)\n- Handle edge cases: duplicate creates, stale deletes, partial failures\n- Implement a batch sync API endpoint on the backend\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/sync/syncEngine.ts` — Background sync orchestrator with queue replay\n- `frontend/src/sync/conflictResolver.ts` — Conflict detection and last-write-wins resolution\n- `frontend/src/components/SyncStatus.tsx` — Sync status indicator (checkmark/spinner/warning)\n- `backend/routes/sync.py` — `POST /api/sync` batch sync endpoint\n- `backend/schemas.py` — Sync-specific request/response models\n- `backend/tests/test_sync.py` — Tests for sync and conflict scenarios\n- Updated service worker with Background Sync API registration\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- After going offline, making 5+ changes, and reconnecting, all changes sync to the server within 15 seconds\n- Sync status indicator shows: ✓ checkmark when fully synced, spinner when syncing, badge with count when pending (\"3 pending\")\n- Hovering over sync indicator shows tooltip with details (\"3 changes waiting to sync\")\n- If the server has a newer `updated_at` for a todo than the local version, the server version wins and local is updated\n- If sync fails due to network error, it retries with exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, max 30s)\n- After 5 consecutive failures, a \"Sync failed — tap to retry\" message appears\n- Deleting a todo offline that was already deleted on the server does not cause an error (idempotent)\n- Creating a todo offline generates a temporary UUID; after sync, the server-assigned ID replaces it transparently\n- `POST /api/sync` accepts `{\"operations\": [{\"type\": \"create\", \"payload\": {...}}, ...]}` and returns per-operation results\n- Each result includes `{\"status\": \"ok\"|\"conflict\"|\"error\", \"data\": {...}}`\n- Backend sync endpoint processes operations in a single database transaction\n- Running `cd backend && python -m pytest tests/test_sync.py` passes with all conflict scenarios covered\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Background Sync API: `registration.sync.register('sync-todos')` in service worker, with fallback polling\n- Sync queue replay: process in FIFO order; a failure for one todo doesn't block other todos\n- Conflict resolution: compare `updated_at` — server wins if server > local for same field\n- Temporary ID mapping: server returns `{\"temp_id\": \"uuid-local\", \"server_id\": \"uuid-server\"}` for creates\n- After sync completes, update IndexedDB with canonical server state and clear processed queue entries\n- Exponential backoff with jitter: `delay = min(base * 2^n, max) + random(0, base)`\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 8: Testing, Error Boundaries & Production Readiness\n\n### Scope\n- Achieve 80%+ test coverage across frontend and backend\n- Add React error boundaries for graceful failure recovery\n- Write Playwright E2E tests for all critical user flows\n- Production build optimization and Docker deployment setup\n- Add structured logging to the backend\n- Final polish pass on error states and edge cases\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/components/ErrorBoundary.tsx` — Error boundary with recovery UI\n- `frontend/src/__tests__/` — Vitest unit tests for components, hooks, and store\n- `frontend/e2e/` — Playwright E2E test suite\n- `frontend/e2e/todo-crud.spec.ts` — CRUD flow tests\n- `frontend/e2e/drag-reorder.spec.ts` — Drag-and-drop tests\n- `frontend/e2e/offline-sync.spec.ts` — Offline mode and sync tests\n- `frontend/e2e/filters-search.spec.ts` — Filter and search tests\n- `backend/tests/` — Expanded pytest suite with edge cases\n- `Dockerfile.frontend` — Multi-stage production build\n- `Dockerfile.backend` — Python production image\n- `docker-compose.yml` — Full-stack development and production setup\n- `backend/middleware/logging.py` — Structured JSON request logging\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- `cd frontend && npm run test` passes with 80%+ line coverage (Vitest)\n- `cd backend && python -m pytest --cov` passes with 80%+ line coverage\n- E2E: create 3 todos, verify order, delete middle one, verify remaining 2\n- E2E: create a todo, go offline (Playwright network emulation), edit it, go online, verify sync\n- E2E: drag first todo to last position, refresh, verify order persisted\n- E2E: toggle dark mode, refresh, verify dark mode persists\n- E2E: search for \"milk\", verify only matching todos shown with highlighted text\n- All E2E tests pass in headless Chromium via `npx playwright test`\n- If a component throws during render, error boundary shows \"Something went wrong\" with a \"Try again\" button\n- `docker-compose up` starts both services; frontend at `localhost:3000`, backend at `localhost:8000`\n- Production frontend build is under 300KB gzipped\n- Backend logs structured JSON: `{\"timestamp\", \"level\", \"request_id\", \"method\", \"path\", \"status\", \"duration_ms\"}`\n- All API errors use consistent format: `{\"detail\": {\"code\": \"NOT_FOUND\", \"message\": \"Todo not found\"}}`\n- Service worker activates correctly in the production build\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Vitest with `@testing-library/react` and `@testing-library/user-event` for frontend tests\n- Test behavior, not implementation: use `getByRole`, `getByText`, `userEvent`\n- Playwright: use `page.context().setOffline(true)` for offline tests\n- Start backend as a test fixture in Playwright `globalSetup`\n- Docker: `node:20-alpine` for frontend build stage, `python:3.12-slim` for backend\n- Multi-stage frontend build: install → build → serve with `nginx:alpine`\n- Error boundary: wrap app root and todo list separately for granular recovery\n- Use `structlog` for Python structured logging\n",
