ader support with ARIA attributes and live regions\n- Micro-interaction refinements (checkbox animation, hover effects)\n- Add keyboard shortcut help dialog (press `?` to show)\n- Focus management (trap in modals, restore after delete)\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` — Theme management with localStorage + system preference\n- `frontend/src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx` — Sun/moon toggle with transition\n- `frontend/src/styles/themes.css` — CSS custom properties for light and dark themes\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useListNavigation.ts` — Arrow key navigation for the todo list\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useKeyboardShortcuts.ts` — Global keyboard shortcut handler\n- `frontend/src/components/KeyboardShortcutHelp.tsx` — Shortcut help overlay/modal\n- `frontend/src/components/FocusTrap.tsx` — Focus trap for modals\n- Updated all components with ARIA roles, labels, and live regions\n- Responsive breakpoints applied to all layout components\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- A theme toggle (sun/moon icon) appears in the header\n- Clicking it switches between light and dark mode with a smooth 200ms color transition\n- On first load, theme matches `prefers-color-scheme` system setting\n- Theme preference persists in localStorage across page reloads\n- In dark mode, all text meets WCAG AA contrast ratio (4.5:1 minimum)\n- Dark mode feels intentional — distinct palette, not just inverted colors\n- On mobile (< 640px): single column, larger touch targets (min 44x44px), drag handle area is wider\n- On tablet (640-1024px): comfortable spacing, hover states active\n- On desktop (> 1024px): centered content with max-width ~640px\n- All interactive elements are reachable via Tab in logical order\n- Pressing Up/Down arrow keys moves focus between todo items\n- Pressing Space on a focused todo toggles completion\n- Screen reader announces each todo as \"Buy milk, incomplete\" or \"Buy milk, complete\"\n- Screen reader announces count changes via `aria-live=\"polite\"` region\n- Completing a todo plays a satisfying checkmark draw animation (not just a state change)\n- Focus returns to the next item when a todo is deleted (or previous if last)\n- Pressing `?` shows a keyboard shortcuts overlay listing all available shortcuts\n- Pressing `n` focuses the new task input\n- Pressing `j`/`k` navigates up/down the task list\n- Focus is trapped inside the shortcut help modal; Escape closes it and returns focus to trigger\n- `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` disables animations\n- Focus rings are visible on keyboard navigation but hidden on mouse interaction (`:focus-visible`)\n\n### Technical Notes\n- CSS custom properties on `:root` and `[data-theme=\"dark\"]` for all colors\n- Use `window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)')` for initial detection\n- Store theme in localStorage key `theme` with values `light`, `dark`, `system`\n- List navigation: `role=\"listbox\"` on container, `role=\"option\"` on items, `aria-activedescendant` for focus\n- Checkbox animation: CSS keyframe animation drawing a checkmark path (SVG or CSS)\n- Mobile breakpoints: 640px (mobile), 768px (tablet), 1024px (desktop)\n- Keyboard shortcuts: register on `document` with `keydown`, check `event.target` to avoid firing in inputs\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 6: IndexedDB Storage & Service Worker\n\n### Scope\n- Set up IndexedDB with the `idb` library as the local persistent store\n- Register a service worker via vite-plugin-pwa for offline asset caching\n- Make the app load and function fully without network connectivity\n- Implement a sync queue for mutations made while offline\n- Add online/offline status indicator in the UI\n- Ensure all existing features (CRUD, reorder, filter, search) work identically offline\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/db/todoDb.ts` — IndexedDB database setup with typed schema and CRUD operations\n- `frontend/src/db/syncQueue.ts` — Sync queue table and operations (FIFO mutation log)\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useOnlineStatus.ts` — Reactive online/offline detection hook\n- `frontend/src/components/OfflineIndicator.tsx` — Banner/badge showing connection state\n- `frontend/src/sw/` — Service worker configuration for vite-plugin-pwa\n- Updated `todoStore.ts` — reads from IndexedDB as source of truth, writes to both IndexedDB and API\n- Updated `vite.config.ts` with vite-plugin-pwa configuration\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- After first visit with network, disconnecting network (DevTools offline mode) does NOT break the app\n- Creating a todo while offline stores it in IndexedDB and shows it in the list immediately\n- Editing a todo while offline updates IndexedDB and the UI immediately\n- Deleting a todo while offline removes it from IndexedDB and the UI\n- Reordering todos while offline persists the new order in IndexedDB\n- Refreshing the page while offline loads all todos from IndexedDB (not a blank screen)\n- A subtle \"Offline\" indicator (badge or banner) appears when network is unavailable\n- The indicator changes to \"Syncing...\" when connectivity is restored\n- The indicator disappears smoothly when sync is complete\n- Filtering, searching, and bulk actions all work offline (they operate on IndexedDB data)\n- The service worker caches the app shell (HTML, JS, CSS) — repeat visits load instantly even offline\n- Chrome DevTools > Application > Service Workers shows the SW as active\n- Chrome DevTools > Application > IndexedDB shows the local task database with data\n- IndexedDB contains a `todos` object store and a `syncQueue` object store\n- Sync queue entries have structure: `{id, type: 'create'|'update'|'delete'|'reorder', payload, timestamp}`\n- Tasks created offline have valid UUIDs (generated client-side via `crypto.randomUUID()`)\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use the `idb` library (lightweight Promise wrapper for IndexedDB)\n- Use `vite-plugin-pwa` with `injectManifest` strategy for maximum control over the service worker\n- Service worker strategies: Cache-First for static assets, Network-First for API GET requests\n- Online detection: combine `navigator.onLine` with `online`/`offline` events; plus periodic `/health` ping\n- The Zustand store should use a \"local-first\" pattern: always write to IndexedDB first, then enqueue a sync operation\n- Generate UUIDs on the client side so offline-created tasks have stable IDs from the moment of creation\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 7: Background Sync & Conflict Resolution\n\n### Scope\n- Build a background sync engine that replays queued mutations when online\n- Implement conflict detection using version counters\n- Build a conflict resolution UI for manual resolution when needed\n- Add a sync status indicator per task\n- Handle edge cases: duplicate creates, stale deletes, concurrent edits\n- Implement a batch sync API endpoint on the backend\n- Add retry logic with exponential backoff\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/sync/syncEngine.ts` — Background sync orchestrator with queue replay\n- `frontend/src/sync/conflictResolver.ts` — Conflict detection and resolution logic\n- `frontend/src/components/ConflictDialog.tsx` — UI for manual conflict resolution\n- `frontend/src/components/SyncStatus.tsx` — Per-task sync indicator (synced/pending/conflict)\n- `backend/routes/sync.py` — `POST /api/v1/sync` batch sync endpoint\n- `backend/tests/test_sync.py` — Tests for sync and conflict scenarios\n- Updated service worker with Background Sync API registration\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- After going offline, making 5+ changes, and reconnecting, all changes sync to the server within 15 seconds\n- Tasks created offline sync to the server automatically when connectivity returns\n- Tasks edited offline sync without user intervention if no conflict exists\n- Tasks deleted offline are deleted on the server upon sync\n- Sync status indicator shows: checkmark when synced, clock when pending, warning when conflict\n- If a task was edited both offline and on the server, a conflict dialog appears showing both versions\n- User can choose \"keep mine\", \"keep server\", or \"merge\" in the conflict dialog\n- After resolving all conflicts, the sync status shows all tasks as \"synced\"\n- If sync fails due to network error, it retries with exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, max 30s)\n- After 5 consecutive failures, a \"Sync failed — tap to retry\" message appears\n- Deleting a todo offline that was already deleted on the server does not cause an error (idempotent)\n- Rapid toggling of online/offline does not produce duplicate tasks\n- `POST /api/v1/sync` accepts `{\"operations\": [...]}` and returns per-operation results with `status: \"ok\"|\"conflict\"|\"error\"`\n- Backend returns `409` when `PUT /api/v1/todos/{id}` receives a stale `version` value\n- The sync queue is cleared only after successful server acknowledgment\n- Running `cd backend && python -m pytest tests/test_sync.py` passes with all conflict scenarios covered\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use an exponential backoff with jitter: `delay = min(base * 2^n, max) + random(0, base)`\n- Process the sync queue in FIFO order to preserve causality\n- The batch sync endpoint should be transactional — all succeed or all fail, with per-item error reporting\n- For auto-resolution: if only non-overlapping fields changed, merge automatically; if the same field changed, prompt the user\n- Version counters increment on every successful write; the server rejects writes with `version < current_version`\n- Use `requestIdleCallback` for sync processing to avoid blocking the UI thread\n- Background Sync API: `registration.sync.register('sync-todos')` in service worker, with fallback polling\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 8: Performance, PWA & Production Build\n\n### Scope\n- Optimize bundle size with code splitting and tree shaking\n- Add PWA manifest for installability (Add to Home Screen)\n- Implement virtual scrolling for large task lists (1000+ items)\n- Add comprehensive error boundaries\n- Performance audit and optimization pass\n- Production build and Docker deployment setup\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/public/manifest.json` — PWA web app manifest with icons\n- `frontend/src/components/VirtualTaskList.tsx` — Virtualized list for performance\n- `frontend/src/components/ErrorBoundary.tsx` — React error boundary with recovery UI\n- PWA icons in multiple sizes (192x192, 512x512)\n- `Dockerfile.frontend` — Multi-stage production build (Node build → nginx serve)\n- `Dockerfile.backend` — Python production image\n- `docker-compose.yml` — Full-stack deployment\n- Performance optimizations: lazy loading, memoization, bundle analysis\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Lighthouse PWA score is 90+\n- Lighthouse Performance score is 90+ on mobile\n- The app is installable via \"Add to Home Screen\" on Chrome and Safari\n- A list of 1000 tasks scrolls at 60fps without dropped frames\n- The initial JS bundle is under 200KB gzipped\n- React error boundary catches component errors and shows a \"Something went wrong\" screen with a retry button\n- Backend response time for `GET /api/v1/todos` with 1000 items is under 100ms\n- `docker-compose up` starts both frontend and backend; frontend at `localhost:3000`, backend at `localhost:8000`\n- Production frontend build is under 300KB gzipped total\n- Service worker activates correctly in the production build\n- No console errors or warnings in production build\n- PWA manifest has `display: \"standalone\"`, appropriate theme colors, and at least two icon sizes\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use `React.lazy` and `Suspense` for code splitting the detail panel and conflict dialog\n- Use `@tanstack/react-virtual` for virtual scrolling\n- Run `npx vite-bundle-visualizer` and eliminate any unexpected large dependencies\n- Use `React.memo` on `TodoItem` to prevent unnecessary re-renders during list operations\n- Docker: `node:20-alpine` for frontend build stage, `python:3.12-slim` for backend\n- Multi-stage frontend build: install → build → serve with `nginx:alpine`\n- Add `Cache-Control` headers for API response