n### Technical Notes\n- Use a command pattern for undo/redo: each action stores a `do` and `undo` operation\n- Bulk operations should use a single API call: `POST /api/v1/todos/bulk` with `{ action, ids, payload? }`\n- Toast notifications should use portal rendering to avoid layout interference\n- Use `zustand/middleware` to implement the undo/redo middleware cleanly\n- Export format: JSON array of todos with all fields, versioned with a `format_version` key\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 10: E2E Tests, Final Polish & Documentation\n\n### Scope\n- Write Playwright E2E tests for all critical user flows\n- Full accessibility audit and fixes (screen reader, keyboard, ARIA)\n- Add onboarding experience for first-time users\n- Final cross-browser testing and bug fixes\n- Write user-facing documentation and README\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/e2e/todo-crud.spec.ts` — CRUD flow tests\n- `frontend/e2e/drag-reorder.spec.ts` — Drag-and-drop tests\n- `frontend/e2e/offline-sync.spec.ts` — Offline mode and sync tests\n- `frontend/e2e/filters-search.spec.ts` — Filter and search tests\n- `frontend/e2e/theme-a11y.spec.ts` — Theme toggle and accessibility tests\n- `frontend/src/components/Onboarding.tsx` — First-run walkthrough\n- Accessibility fixes across all components (ARIA labels, roles, live regions)\n- `README.md` with setup instructions, architecture overview, and screenshots\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- E2E: create 3 todos, verify order, delete middle one, verify remaining 2\n- E2E: create a todo, go offline (Playwright network emulation), edit it, go online, verify sync\n- E2E: drag first todo to last position, refresh, verify order persisted\n- E2E: toggle dark mode, refresh, verify dark mode persists\n- E2E: search for \"milk\", verify only matching todos shown with highlighted text\n- All E2E tests pass in headless Chromium via `npx playwright test`\n- All interactive elements are reachable and operable via keyboard alone\n- Screen reader (VoiceOver/NVDA) can navigate and operate the full app\n- ARIA live regions announce dynamic changes (\"Task added\", \"3 tasks deleted\", \"Now offline\")\n- First-time users see a brief 3-step onboarding walkthrough explaining core features\n- Onboarding can be dismissed and does not reappear (stored in localStorage)\n- No WCAG AA violations reported by axe-core automated scan\n- The app works in Chrome, Firefox, and Safari (latest versions)\n- README includes: project description, prerequisites, setup steps, architecture diagram, and available scripts\n- `cd frontend && npm run test` passes with 80%+ line coverage\n- `cd backend && python -m pytest --cov` passes with 80%+ line coverage\n- No TypeScript errors (`npx tsc --noEmit` passes)\n- No ESLint errors in the final build\n",
