n image.\n- `docker-compose.yml` — Full-stack deployment.\n- `README.md` with setup instructions, architecture overview, and screenshots.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- E2E: create 3 todos, verify order, delete middle one, verify remaining 2.\n- E2E: create a todo, go offline (Playwright network emulation), edit it, go online, verify sync.\n- E2E: drag first todo to last position, refresh, verify order persisted.\n- E2E: toggle dark mode, refresh, verify dark mode persists.\n- E2E: search for \"milk\", verify only matching todos shown with highlighted text.\n- All E2E tests pass in headless Chromium via `npx playwright test`.\n- Lighthouse PWA score is 90+.\n- Lighthouse Performance score is 90+ on mobile.\n- The initial JS bundle is under 200KB gzipped.\n- Backend response time for `GET /api/v1/todos` with 1000 items is under 100ms.\n- `docker-compose up` starts both frontend and backend; app is accessible on port 80.\n- React error boundary catches component errors and shows \"Something went wrong\" with retry button.\n- No console errors or warnings in production build.\n- All interactive elements are reachable and operable via keyboard alone.\n- No WCAG AA violations reported by axe-core automated scan.\n- The app works in Chrome, Firefox, and Safari (latest versions).\n- README includes: project description, prerequisites, setup steps, architecture diagram, and available scripts.\n- `cd frontend && npm run test` passes with 80%+ line coverage.\n- `cd backend && python -m pytest --cov` passes with 80%+ line coverage.\n- No TypeScript errors (`npx tsc --noEmit` passes).\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use Playwright for E2E tests — it handles Service Workers and offline simulation well.\n- Use `React.lazy` and `Suspense` for code splitting the command palette and conflict dialog.\n- Run `npx vite-bundle-visualizer` to eliminate unexpected large dependencies.\n- Docker: `node:20-alpine` for frontend build stage, `python:3.12-slim` for backend.\n- Multi-stage frontend bui