 (triggered when gap < 0.0001)\n- Backend: the `reorder` endpoint takes `after_id` (the item this should appear after) and calculates the new fractional position server-side\n- DnD Kit's `useSortable` gives us `transform` and `transition` for smooth animations out of the box\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 4: Offline Storage with IndexedDB\n\n### Scope\n- Implement IndexedDB storage layer for todos\n- Cache all todos locally for offline read access\n- Service worker for app shell caching\n- Offline detection and status indicator in the UI\n- Read operations work fully offline from IndexedDB\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/storage/db.ts` — IndexedDB wrapper (using `idb` library)\n- `frontend/src/storage/todoStore.ts` — Todo-specific IndexedDB operations\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useOnlineStatus.ts` — Hook for detecting online/offline state\n- `frontend/src/components/OfflineIndicator.tsx` — Banner/badge showing offline status\n- `frontend/public/sw.js` (or Vite PWA plugin config) — Service worker for caching\n- `frontend/vite.config.ts` — Updated with PWA plugin configuration\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useTodos.ts` — Updated to read from IndexedDB first, then sync with server\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- When the app loads online, all todos are cached to IndexedDB\n- When the user goes offline (simulated via DevTools > Network > Offline), the app still displays all previously loaded todos\n- The offline indicator appears within 2 seconds of losing connection, showing \"You're offline — changes will sync when you reconnect\"\n- The offline indicator disappears within 2 seconds of regaining connection\n- Refreshing the page while offline still loads the app shell and displays cached todos\n- The service worker caches all static assets (HTML, JS, CSS, images) for offline app shell\n- IndexedDB data survives browser restart (open app offline after browser restart — data is present)\n- No console errors appear when operating offline\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use the `idb` library for a promise-based IndexedDB wrapper — much cleaner than raw API\n- Use `vite-plugin-pwa` for service worker generation and precaching\n- IndexedDB schema: object store \"todos\" with keyPath \"id\" and index on \"position\"\n- Sync strategy for this sprint is read-only offline; write operations queue in Sprint 5\n- `useOnlineStatus` hook should use both `navigator.onLine` and periodic pings to `/health` for reliable detection (some browsers lie about `onLine`)\n- Cache invalidation: on reconnect, fetch fresh data from server and update IndexedDB\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 5: Offline Write Operations & Sync Queue\n\n### Scope\n- Enable full CRUD operations while offline\n- Implement an operation queue that logs all mutations\n- Replay queue against the backend when coming back online\n- Handle sync conflicts with last-write-wins strategy\n- Visual sync progress indicator\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/sync/operationQueue.ts` — Queue for offline mutations stored in IndexedDB\n- `frontend/src/sync/syncEngine.ts` — Replays queued operations on reconnect\n- `frontend/src/sync/conflictResolver.ts` — Last-write-wins conflict resolution\n- `frontend/src/components/SyncStatus.tsx` — Shows sync progress (pending changes count, syncing animation, synced confirmation)\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useTodos.ts` — Updated for offline-first write path\n- `backend/routes/sync.py` — Batch sync endpoint `POST /api/sync`\n- `backend/models.py` — Updated with sync-related models\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- User can add a new todo while offline; it appears immediately in the list with a \"pending sync\" indicator (e.g., a small cloud icon with an arrow)\n- User can edit a todo title while offline; the change is saved locally and shows pending sync indicator\n- User can delete a todo while offline; it disappears from the list and is queued for server deletion\n- User can reorder todos while offline; the new order is preserved locally\n- When coming back online, all queued operations sync automatically within 5 seconds\n- During sync, a progress indicator shows \"Syncing 3 changes...\" with a count\n- After successful sync, a brief \"All changes synced\" confirmation appears for 3 seconds\n- `POST /api/sync` accepts a batch of operations `[{ op: \"create\"|\"update\"|\"delete\", data: {...}, timestamp: \"...\" }]` and returns results for each\n- If the server has a newer version of a todo (updated_at > client's timestamp), the server version wins and the client is notified with a subtle toast: \"Task 'X' was updated on another device\"\n- After sync, client and server data are consistent (verified by comparing `GET /api/todos` with IndexedDB contents)\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Operation queue schema: `{ id, type: \"create\"|\"update\"|\"delete\"|\"reorder\", payload, timestamp, status: \"pending\"|\"syncing\"|\"failed\" }`\n- Queue operations are ordered by timestamp and replayed in order\n- The batch sync endpoint processes operations transactionally — all succeed or roll back\n- For conflict detection: compare `updated_at` timestamps; server value always wins on conflict\n- Failed operations should be retried up to 3 times with exponential backoff\n- After queue drain, do a full data reconciliation: `GET /api/todos?since={last_sync_timestamp}`\n- Handle the edge case: user deletes a todo offline, but it was edited on server — server deletion should still succeed\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 6: Polish, Animations & Micro-interactions\n\n### Scope\n- Add thoughtful animations and transitions throughout the app\n- Keyboard shortcuts for power users\n- Toast notification system for feedback\n- Responsive design for mobile and desktop\n- Dark mode with system preference detection\n- Focus management and accessibility improvements\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/components/Toast.tsx` and `frontend/src/hooks/useToast.ts` — Toast notification system\n- `frontend/src/styles/animations.css` — Shared animation definitions\n- `frontend/src/styles/theme.css` — CSS custom properties for light/dark themes\n- `frontend/src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx` — Dark/light mode switch\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useKeyboardShortcuts.ts` — Global keyboard shortcut handler\n- `frontend/src/components/KeyboardShortcutsHelp.tsx` — Modal showing available shortcuts\n- Updated component styles for responsive layouts and accessibility\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Adding a todo triggers a slide-in animation from the top of the list\n- Completing a todo plays a satisfying checkmark animation (CSS) and the item smoothly moves to a \"completed\" section at the bottom (if section exists) or fades the text with strikethrough animation\n- Deleting shows a slide-out animation before removal\n- Reorder drop has a subtle bounce animation on landing\n- Toast notifications appear for: sync complete, sync conflict, offline mode entered, error states\n- Keyboard shortcuts work: `N` to focus the new todo input, `Escape` to blur inputs, `?` to show shortcut help, `D` to toggle dark mode\n- The app is fully usable on a 375px-wide mobile screen — input field and buttons are touch-friendly (min 44px tap targets)\n- Dark mode activates automatically based on system preference (`prefers-color-scheme`)\n- User can manually toggle dark mode; the preference persists in localStorage\n- All interactive elements have visible focus indicators for keyboard navigation\n- Color contrast meets WCAG AA standards (4.5:1 for normal text)\n- Screen reader announces: new todo added, todo completed, todo deleted, sync status changes (via `aria-live` regions)\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use CSS custom properties for theming: `--color-bg`, `--color-text`, `--color-accent`, etc., switching values via a `.dark` class on `<html>`\n- Keep animations under 300ms for responsiveness; use `prefers-reduced-motion` media query to disable animations for users who prefer it\n- Toast system: max 3 visible toasts, auto-dismiss after 4 seconds, stack from bottom-right on desktop, bottom-center on mobile\n- Keyboard shortcut handler should be a top-level hook that doesn't fire when user is typing in an input\n- Use `ResizeObserver` or CSS container queries for responsive layout rather than just media queries\n- Announce list changes to screen readers with `aria-live=\"polite\"` on the todo list container\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 7: Search, Filter & Bulk Operations\n\n### Scope\n- Add search/filter functionality to quickly find todos\n- Filter by status: all, active, completed\n- Bulk operations: mark all complete, delete all completed\n- Todo count summary\n- Backend search endpoint with query support\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/src/components/SearchBar.tsx` — Search input with debounced filtering\n- `frontend/src/components/FilterTabs.tsx` — All / Active / Completed filter tabs\n- `frontend/src/components/BulkActions.tsx` — Buttons for bulk operations\n- `frontend/src/components/TodoCount.tsx` — Summary line (e.g., \"3 items left\")\n- `backend/routes/todos.py` — Updated `GET /api/todos` with `?q=search&status=active|completed|all` query params\n- `frontend/src/hooks/useTodos.ts` — Updated with search and filter state\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- A search input at the top filters todos in real-time as the user types (debounced 200ms)\n- Searching for \"gro\" shows only todos whose title contains \"gro\" (case-insensitive)\n- Clearing the search field shows all todos again\n- Filter tabs \"All\", \"Active\", \"Completed\" filter the list; the active tab is visually highlighted\n- \"3 items left\" counter shows the number of uncompleted todos, updating in real-time\n- \"Mark all complete\" button marks all visible (filtered) todos as completed in one click\n- \"Clear completed\" button deletes all completed todos with a confirmation dialog\n- `GET /api/todos?q=groceries&status=active` returns only active todos matching \"groceries\"\n- Search and filter work offline (filtering IndexedDB data locally)\n- Bulk operations work offline (queued to sync queue)\n- When the list is