cker, and priority selector\n- Description field supports multi-line text up to 2000 characters, with a character counter\n- Due date picker shows a calendar; selecting a date displays it as a relative date badge (\"Today\", \"Tomorrow\", \"Mar 15\", \"Overdue!\")\n- Overdue todos show a red \"Overdue\" badge next to the due date\n- Priority is displayed as a colored left border or dot: none (no indicator), low (blue), medium (yellow), high (red)\n- Sort selector allows switching between \"Manual order\", \"Due date (soonest first)\", and \"Priority (highest first)\"\n- Sorting by due date places todos without a due date at the end\n- All new fields persist correctly through the API (create with fields, retrieve with fields)\n- New fields work offline (stored in IndexedDB, synced when online)\n- `POST /api/todos` with `{ \"title\": \"Test\", \"description\": \"Details\", \"due_date\": \"2026-04-01\", \"priority\": \"high\" }` returns the todo with all fields populated\n- Backend migration runs cleanly on existing data (existing todos get `null` for new optional fields)\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Due date stored as ISO 8601 date string in SQLite (TEXT column) — no timezone complexity needed\n- Priority as an enum: `none`, `low`, `medium`, `high` — stored as TEXT in SQLite\n- The detail panel should animate open/closed with height transition\n- Use fractional indexing for manual sort, SQL `ORDER BY` for date/priority sorts\n- When sorted by date or priority, drag-and-drop reordering should be disabled (with a tooltip explaining why)\n- IndexedDB migration: add new fields with defaults to existing objects on version upgrade\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 9: Testing & Error Handling Hardening\n\n### Scope\n- Comprehensive test coverage across frontend and backend\n- Error boundary components for graceful failure handling\n- Retry logic for failed API calls\n- Input sanitization and edge case handling\n- Performance optimization (virtual scrolling for large lists, memoization)\n\n##