r) for mocking API calls in frontend tests\n- Virtual scrolling: use `@tanstack/react-virtual` for rendering only visible rows\n- Error boundary should log errors to console in development, and could post to an error tracking service in production\n- Test the sync engine with simulated offline/online transitions\n- SQLite handles concurrent reads well but serializes writes — use WAL mode for better concurrent read performance\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 10: Production Build, PWA & Final Polish\n\n### Scope\n- Production-ready build configuration\n- Full PWA manifest with install prompt\n- App icons and splash screens\n- Performance audit and optimization (Lighthouse 90+)\n- README with setup instructions and screenshots\n- Docker configuration for easy deployment\n\n### Deliverables\n- `frontend/public/manifest.json` — PWA manifest with app name, icons, theme colors\n- `frontend/public/icons/` — App icons in all required sizes (192x192, 512x512, maskable)\n- `frontend/src/components/InstallPrompt.tsx` — Custom PWA install prompt\n- `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml` — Containerized frontend and backend\n- `README.md` — Setup instructions, screenshots, architecture overview\n- `frontend/vite.config.ts` — Optimized production build config (code splitting, compression)\n- `backend/main.py` — Production-ready with proper logging, error handling, static file serving\n- Lighthouse audit results in the repo\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- `npm run build` produces a production bundle under 200KB (gzipped, excluding icons)\n- The app is installable as a PWA on Chrome and Safari — \"Add to Home Screen\" prompt appears\n- Installed PWA launches with the correct app icon, name \"Todo\", and theme color\n- Installed PWA works fully offline (app shell loads, cached data displayed, mutations queued)\n- Lighthouse Performance score >= 90, Accessibility score >= 95, Best Practices >= 90, PWA badge present\n- `docker-compose up` starts both frontend and backend, accessible at `localhost:300