heme tokens\n- `frontend/src/components/ThemeToggle.tsx` — Dark/light mode toggle button\n- `frontend/src/components/ProgressBar.tsx` — Visual progress indicator\n- `frontend/src/components/ErrorBoundary.tsx` — React error boundary with retry\n- `frontend/src/styles/animations.css` — Shared animation keyframes and transitions\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- The app automatically uses dark mode if the system preference is set to dark\n- Clicking the theme toggle switches between light and dark mode with a smooth transition (no flash)\n- Theme preference is persisted in localStorage and survives page refreshes\n- Adding a new todo animates it sliding in from the top with a subtle fade\n- Deleting a todo animates it sliding out with a fade\n- Checking a todo plays a satisfying check animation (e.g., the checkbox fills with a bouncing circle)\n- A progress bar at the top shows \"3 of 7 completed\" with a colored fill\n- On mobile (< 768px), touch targets are at least 44x44px\n- Swipe left on a todo (mobile) reveals a delete action\n- An unhandled error in a component shows a friendly \"Something went wrong\" message with a \"Try again\" button instead of a blank screen\n- The overall design is visually cohesive with consistent spacing (8px grid), typography scale, and color palette\n\n### Technical Notes\n- Use `prefers-color-scheme` media query for auto-detection, `data-theme` attribute on `<html>` for manual override.\n- Animations should respect `prefers-reduced-motion` — disable or simplify animations when set.\n- Use CSS `@keyframes` for simple animations, Framer Motion only for complex gestures (swipe-to-delete).\n- The progress bar should use CSS `conic-gradient` or a simple filled bar — no heavy charting library.\n- Mobile swipe gesture: use Pointer Events with velocity detection for a natural feel.\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 10: Testing, Performance & Production Readiness\n\n### Scope\n- Achieve 80%+ test coverage across frontend and backend.\n- Add end-to-end tests for